          "date": "2012-04-08 06:47:46.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-957 scrub: tirgger OI scrub if found bad OI entry",
        "message": "LU-957 scrub: tirgger OI scrub if found bad OI entry\n\nIf some RPC triggers OI lookup and finds inconsistent OI mapping,\nit should trigger OI scrub to check and repair the inconsistency.\n\nWhen the fid is returned to client, the OI mapping corresponding\nto such fid may be not updated, or not committed to disk yet. If\nserver crashed before OI scrub completed, then recovery with the\nfid corresponding to inconsistent OI mapping will fail.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <yong.fan@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I28045bc10e187d83e10b4a7fe290d4385e4d1da0\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
